Articles.Content:
About a week ago (as of 1/24/2014) I started a YouTube channel for my KSP career let's play series... If anyone is interested, the username is SpaceWooperts

Channel Link: https://www.youtube.com/user/spacewooperts

Latest Video:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WlLrh58wRlE&list=PLcRT4JeBK7rphmMkHHD--1Fpa6DJAWndc&index=5

The install for that I play on has mods, the list will be kept here as well.

Any questions are welcome, criticism is good too. I'm a first time video maker so I'm not good at "smiling for the camera." My skills for commentary and video editing are still improving drastically over what they were a week ago.

Mods:

Kethane: http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/23979-Kethane-Pack-0-8-4-Find-it-mine-it-burn-it!-Now-w-Toolbar-Critical-bug-fixed

Bump. No replies yet + new video.

Added some more videos (haven't updated the thread yet)

Bump

Also, need to get some replies for this question: should I finish this career or start a new one with new mods for a better roleplay? I want to sort of brush over how the real space program worked while still keeping it "Kerbal."

This career was started before I started making videos.
